{"id":"goldsmith","term":"Goldsmith","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:8\">Neh. 3:8</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:32\">32</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 40:19\">Isa. 40:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 41:7\">41:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 46:6\">46:6</a>). The word so rendered means properly a founder or finer.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Nehemiah 3:8","Nehemiah 3:32","Isaiah 40:19","Isaiah 41:7","Isaiah 46:6"]}